node.text:
The most affected region by Coronavirus in Italy 💔 Lombardia is located in the center of Italy and Europe. Home to a variety of industries such as agriculture, manufacturing, fashion and eco-tourism. ⠀

The breathtaking landscape of Lombardy is a mixture of hills, mountains, lakes and plains. Its Alpine area is very popular in winter by skiers. Nature lovers are greeted by beautiful shoreline along the great Lombard lakes: Lake Garda, Lake Como, Lake Maggiore and Lake Iseo. ⠀

Stay strong Italy! 💚🤍❤️ #ForzaItalia

Video by @idressitalian ⠀

Always #wondermore

Visit: https://wonderlustcollective.co

COSTA RICA STAY GIVEAWAY!! 🌴 🇨🇷 

We are giving you and a friend a chance to win an epic trip to Costa Rica! 

The winner will receive 5 days/4 nights and 2x $500 airplane ticket credit to stay at the beautiful eco-luxury glamping hotel @colinasecretaglamping in Puerto Viejo Limón, Costa Rica. 

Enjoy the lovely tropical beaches, grand adventures and the wonders of nature of Costa Rica!

To Enter:
1) Follow @colinasecretaglamping, @wonderlustcollective + @dailypnut 
2) Tag friends in separate comments
3) Visit the link in our bio and enter your email
1 Comment = 1 Entry. Unlimited Entries
**BONUS** Share this Post in your Story and Tag Us

A winner will be chosen on July 30th and announced via @wonderlustcollective. 

Winner has until the end of July 2022 to reserve. Not redeemable for cash value.
*
Subject to availability with limitations in Christmas and New Year.
*
Travel to and from location is not provided
-
We will never DM you any links to claim prize!
-
Good luck!! ❤️
-

node.text:
⠀
Meet Neron the Black Jaguar - He has most incredible markings you’ll ever see on a feline! 🤩🐈‍⬛

📸 by @thebigcatsanctuaryuk

Jaguars are the largest felines in the Americas. Adult males can reach an overall length of more than 7 feet, and can weigh anywhere from 150 to 200 pounds. 

Their coats color and markings are very similar to the leopard, with a rich tawny or yellow background with large black rosettes and spots. They have larger heads, more compact bodies, and much more powerful paws! 

The Jaguar also occurs with an all black (melanistic) coat, and like the leopard, the spots can still be seen on black individuals. Albino individuals have been reported as well.

#wondermore

node.text:
⠀
Incredible Fireworks show at Festa del Redentore in Venice, Italy 🎆🇮🇹🎇

Festa del Redentore (Feast of the Redeemer) is one of the most important events in Venice to commemorate the end of a terrible plague that occurred in 1577.

A 330-meter pontoon bridge connects the mainland to the Island of Giudecca allowing you to visit the Basilica of Palladio, which was built after the plague.

Every year, on the third weekend of July, the citizens of Venice together with many tourists from around the world, celebrate the anniversary of this event for two days. The highlights of this festival are the impressive fireworks show on Saturday night and the regattas of traditional Venetian boats.

🎥 by @claudia_mimejorvenecia

📍Venice, Italy 

#wondermore
